  client is not being overwhelmed by data faster than it can handle. bookmark A bookmark is a token representing some state of the database. By passing one or multiple bookmarks along with a query, the server will make sure that the query does not get executed before the represented state(s) have been established. transaction function A transaction function is a callback executed by an executeRead or executeWrite call. The driver automatically re-executes the callback in case of server failure. Driver A Driver object holds the details required to establish connections with a Neo4j database. Quic
