  eo4j Java Driver Manual Installation Raise an issue Installation To start creating a Neo4j Java application, you first need to install the Java driver and get a Neo4j database instance to connect to. Server compatibility The latest driver in the 5.28.x series supports connection to Neo4j instances version 4.4.x, 5.x, 2025.x, and 2026.x. Some of the features introduced in the server in versions 2025.01 and later are not available via the driver version 5.28.x ; use the latest version instead. The driver requires Java 17 or higher. Install the driver If you already have a Maven project, you may 
  lication, you first need to install the Java driver and get a Neo4j database instance to connect to. Server compatibility The latest driver in the 5.28.x series supports connection to Neo4j instances version 4.4.x, 5.x, 2025.x, and 2026.x. Some of the features introduced in the server in versions 2025.01 and later are not available via the driver version 5.28.x ; use the latest version instead. The driver requires Java 17 or higher. Install the driver If you already have a Maven project, you may add the driver as a dependency in your pom.xml file: <dependency> <groupId>org.neo4j.driver</groupI
