onder if native images might require testcontainers' reachability if tests are using it. This makes me think it might be safer to avoid using Testcontainers altogether in native images. It’s important I get this right to prevent any complications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing for Graph Database**\\n\\nI'm considering that meaningful coverage of GraphDatabase.driver/session/query requires a live Neo4j setup. The runtime dependencies appear to be self-contained, so no extra Maven dependencies are needed. I should take action to prepare for this advisory. It’s important to ensure that the JSON is valid, without any newline issues. Ultimately, I want to end up with a final, single JSON object only to maintain clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The Neo4j Java Driver is normally used by creating a Driver for a Neo4j URI and verifying/querying a live database; artifact dependencies are otherwise self-contained, but meaningful driver/session/query coverage needs a Neo4j server.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26.12\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j\",\n      \"reason\": \"Neo4j 5.26 is an LTS server line compatible with the 5.28.x Java driver and provides a local Bolt endpoint for exercising GraphDatabase.driver, sessions, transactions, and executable queries.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"If tests start a local Neo4j process/container, configure authentication deterministically, for example disable auth with NEO4J_AUTH=none or set a known neo4j/<password> credential, expose/map Bolt port 7687, wait until the driver can verifyConnectivity(), and close Driver/session/container resources after tests. Avoid relying on an external Neo4j instance.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Container startup can be slow; tests need an explicit readiness wait rather than a fixed sleep.\",\n    \"Default Neo4j Docker authentication prompts for password change unless NEO4J_AUTH is set, so unconfigured containers can make tests flaky or unusable.\",\n    \"Existing value/mapping tests can exercise some metadata without a server, so local Gradle/native-image verification should remain the final authority on whether the Docker-backed coverage is necessary for the specific fix.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0757e3c1f4b1086a016a427d8679f48193866546cf3c1fd32f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1282, "output": 1178, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35228, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782742390967, "responseId": "resp_0757e3c1f4b1086a016a427d77c3d88193bf6a2f5d502e9779"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Testcontainers metadata**\n\nI'm thinking about the implications of generating metadata for Testcontainers. It seems problematic because the TCK user-code-filter is limited to just org.neo4j.driver, but the classpath includes Testcontainers. I wonder if native images might require testcontainers' reachability if tests are using it. This makes me think it might be safer to avoid using Testcontainers altogether in native images. It’s important I get this right to prevent any complications!\n\n**Preparing for Graph Database**\n\nI'm considering that meaningful coverage of GraphDatabase.driver/session/query requires a live Neo4j setup. The runtime dependencies appear to be self-contained, so no extra Maven dependencies are needed. I should take action to prepare for this advisory. It’s important to ensure that the JSON is valid, without any newline issues. Ultimately, I want to end up with a final, single JSON object only to maintain clarity.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0757e3c1f4b1086a016a427d7897b081938744a93c2d289787\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQn2GcCMNbN-ht2M30i9hLR3WCbN5sRu73PQAoebIwJ1XaGYaoJDIp68aRJHxPJSpJfOmSDJLxqXlp2Tkrzi-GfzmS97DehgVGn3dB5RO5p-EtOJba-3bS_PEBFkzyRFIwoKTIqQvkDd2HRomydWxi9OZwvb_RdHfuklY9vzon8sb0-r1sEAxmjDyhDNq8up6qOTwz87LmInPvS3KtUjSQVtHWuy3I1vqpB9Xv48huhs41T85NlPveeYnYMcxfYiY4VIttauCAc_N7B6gzccyMqgpTPvPf2nuV7s1pcqU__BMiM8lXVrpXEObiHBwrQHe67OmauZiIWX3mfOT9FFnyAdrRcOGmK4kGc3wzUnYfW2RmRTtsOe1dm6oDfCSu01jTp2k_YIjtFtYI1XGyQgSPhJypyNSQI6gx6nx_6tkglYUNtVECRWSeeiQpGuwv0PnHddpwFPihiqzEP8ePrqcYBUBSm6HPpg9GjJuYw8FpX5PyGZeWFSWwcPVK8xRvEzQ2riqusDbaVwkEv-SyGHK4p9zFaNJTdPxzRI-RPcpfapKMpzj-LWsh4Z7QjIcGc8u56jeS4L3QMMU2fSap5x9QqOWuwk3enbWE4OcMgfYxJyOmvFRZ8toNne74XQp-EA1JLfcmYeAhlFkqxRifLQcnLHG-n0xtBFappexiMnuXrXL7rjmcFkuvylr_jV1S9Gk1nWnIQk8VNz-ncEc4LPwwamNZa77ISQJjCTijItUQtczvqoUVkrAkaHOWk8pwa