er if native images might require testcontainers' reachability if tests are using it. This makes me think it might be safer to avoid using Testcontainers altogether in native images. It’s important I get this right to prevent any complications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing for Graph Database**\\n\\nI'm considering that meaningful coverage of GraphDatabase.driver/session/query requires a live Neo4j setup. The runtime dependencies appear to be self-contained, so no extra Maven dependencies are needed. I should take action to prepare for this advisory. It’s important to ensure that the JSON is valid, without any newline issues. Ultimately, I want to end up with a final, single JSON object only to maintain clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The Neo4j Java Driver is normally used by creating a Driver for a Neo4j URI and verifying/querying a live database; artifact dependencies are otherwise self-contained, but meaningful driver/session/query coverage needs a Neo4j server.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26.12\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j\",\n      \"reason\": \"Neo4j 5.26 is an LTS server line compatible with the 5.28.x Java driver and provides a local Bolt endpoint for exercising GraphDatabase.driver, sessions, transactions, and executable queries.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"If tests start a local Neo4j process/container, configure authentication deterministically, for example disable auth with NEO4J_AUTH=none or set a known neo4j/<password> credential, expose/map Bolt port 7687, wait until the driver can verifyConnectivity(), and close Driver/session/container resources after tests. Avoid relying on an external Neo4j instance.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Container startup can be slow; tests need an explicit readiness wait rather than a fixed sleep.\",\n    \"Default Neo4j Docker authentication prompts for password change unless NEO4J_AUTH is set, so unconfigured containers can make tests flaky or unusable.\",\n    \"Existing value/mapping tests can exercise some metadata without a server, so local Gradle/native-image verification should remain the final authority on whether the Docker-backed coverage is necessary for the specific fix.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0757e3c1f4b1086a016a427d8679f48193866546cf3c1fd32f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1282, "output": 1178, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35228, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782742390967, "responseId": "resp_0757e3c1f4b1086a016a427d77c3d88193bf6a2f5d502e9779"}, "toolResults": []}
